Label: Report Frequency
Comment: Frequency of indicator update in report, e.g. daily or monthly. This is used with the reporting style to determine the exact frequency and lag of indicator reports.Note that datasets have their own -Frequency of data updates- field to state how often they are updated.
Source: OAHP Data Catalogue Schema Proposal v05.13
Creator: Rob Brennan, ADAPT UCD

Label: Indicator Type
Comment: Specifies if the indicator has both a numerator and a denominator, is coverage, accumulated or qualitative type
Source: OAHP Data Catalogue Schema Proposal v05.13
Creator: Rob Brennan, ADAPT UCD

Label: Status
Comment: An internal prioritisation process status for the dataset or indicator
Source: OAHP Data Catalogue Schema Proposal v05.13
Creator: Rob Brennan, ADAPT UCD

Label: Numerator Source Dataset
Comment: Identifier, e.g. URL, for the dataset providing a numerator data element. If there are multiple numerator data elements then multiple datasets must be provided as a list.
Source: OAHP Data Catalogue Schema Proposal v05.13
Creator: Rob Brennan, ADAPT UCD

Label: Denominator Source Dataset
Comment: Identifier, e.g. URL, for the dataset providing a denominator data element. If there are multiple denominator data elements then multiple datasets must be provided as a list.
Source: OAHP Data Catalogue Schema Proposal v05.13
Creator: Rob Brennan, ADAPT UCD

Label: Domain
Comment: The high-level category the indicator falls under (e.g. Demography).
Source: OAHP Data Catalogue Schema Proposal v05.13
Creator: Rob Brennan, ADAPT UCD

Label: Subdomain
Comment: A more specific category under the domain (e.g. Population numbers).
Source: OAHP Data Catalogue Schema Proposal v05.13
Creator: Rob Brennan, ADAPT UCD

Label: Other Identifiers
Comment: Alternative identifiers for this indicator from other data publishers or coding schemes (as URIs)
Source: OAHP Data Catalogue Schema Proposal v05.13
Creator: Rob Brennan, ADAPT UCD

Label: Applicable Legislation
Comment: The legislation that mandates the creation or management of the Dataset.
Creator: Rob Brennan, ADAPT UCD
